-- Henderson Says Chief Financial Officer Garrood Plans to Retire
-- B y   J e s s e   W e s t b r o o k
-- 2013-04-12T06:39:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-12/henderson-says-chief-financial-officer-garrood-plans-to-retire.html
Henderson Group Plc (HGG) , a U.K.-based
investment firm that manages 65.7 billion pounds ($101 billion),
said Chief Financial Officer Shirley Garrood is retiring.  Garrood will give up her CFO role and step down as a
director on July 1 after 12 years with the firm, London-based
Henderson said in a statement today. She will be replaced by
Roger Thompson, who was previously global chief operating
officer of the investment-management business at  JPMorgan Chase
& Co. (JPM) ’s asset-management unit, it said.  Garrood will stay at the company through March 2014 to
enable a “smooth transition” and finish projects the company
is working on, Henderson Chairman Rupert Pennant-Rea said in the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
